                                  java.util.ArrayList<RoomDayTime> roomDayTimes,
                                  java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> specialInstruments)
        This method executes the Hungarian Algorithm and returns a HungarianResult.
        Parameters:

        roomDayTimes - an ArrayList that holds RoomDayTimes objects
        specialInstruments - an ArrayList that holds all of the special instruments associated with any rooms

      • createOriginalMatrix

        public static int[][] createOriginalMatrix(java.util.ArrayList<Pair> pairs,
                                           java.util.ArrayList<RoomDayTime> roomDayTimes,
                                           java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> specialInstruments)
        Creates the original 2-D matrix from the randomly generated pairs and RoomDayTimes to start the Hungarian Algorithm.
        Parameters:
        pairs - an ArrayList that holds Pair objects that are to be scheduled
        roomDayTimes - an ArrayList that holds RoomDayTimes objects
        specialInstruments - an ArrayList that holds all of the special instruments associated with any rooms
        Returns:
        A matrix populated with the number representing the score of the pair if the pair can have a lesson in a particular RoomDayTime, or a 0 if the pair is not compatible with a RoomDayTime

      • createMinMatrix

        public static int[][] createMinMatrix(int[][] originalMatrix)
        Finds the maximum value in the matrix and replaces every element with the difference of the maximum and that value. The Hungarian Algorithm is designed to find the minimum result and in this problem the desire is to maximize the score. Assumes a square matrix.
        Parameters:
        originalMatrix - a 2-D matrix with the originally populated scores
        Returns:
        An inverted matrix of the originalMatrix

      • rowReduce

        public static void rowReduce(int[][] matrix)
        Finds the minimum element in every row and replaces every element with the difference between it and the minimum in the row. Assumes a square matrix.
        Parameters:
        matrix - a 2-D matrix
